defs.docs:
An implementation of the
[Aho-Corasick string search algorithm](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aho%E2%80%93Corasick_string_matching_algorithm).

defs.name: Automaton
defs.docs:
An abstraction over automatons and their corresponding iterators.
 The type parameter `P` is the type of the pattern that was used to
 construct this Automaton.

defs.name: next_state
defs.value: fn (&self, si: StateIdx, b: u8) -> StateIdx
defs.docs: Return the next state given the current state and next character.

defs.name: has_match
defs.value: fn (&self, si: StateIdx, outi: usize) -> bool
defs.docs:
Return true if and only if the given state and current pattern index
 indicate a match.

defs.name: get_match
defs.value: fn (&self, si: StateIdx, outi: usize, texti: usize) -> Match
defs.docs: Build a match given the current state, pattern index and input index.

defs.name: start_bytes
defs.docs: Return the set of bytes that have transitions in the root state.

defs.name: patterns
defs.docs: Returns all of the patterns matched by this automaton.

defs.name: pattern
defs.docs: Returns the pattern indexed at `i`.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Return the number of patterns in the automaton.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the automaton has no patterns.

defs.name: find
defs.value: fn <'a, 's, Q> (&'a self, s: &'s Q) -> Matches<'a, 's, P, Self>
defs.docs: Returns an iterator of non-overlapping matches in `s`.

defs.name: find_overlapping
defs.value: fn <'a, 's, Q> (&'a self, s: &'s Q) -> MatchesOverlapping<'a, 's, P, Self>
defs.docs: Returns an iterator of overlapping matches in `s`.

defs.name: stream_find
defs.value: fn <'a, R> (&'a self, rdr: R) -> StreamMatches<'a, R, P, Self>
defs.docs: Returns an iterator of non-overlapping matches in the given reader.

defs.name: stream_find_overlapping
defs.value: fn <'a, R> (&'a self, rdr: R) -> StreamMatchesOverlapping<'a, R, P, Self>
defs.docs: Returns an iterator of overlapping matches in the given reader.

defs.name: Match
defs.docs: Records a match in the search text.

defs.name: pati
defs.docs: The pattern index.

defs.name: start
defs.docs: The starting byte offset of the match in the search text.

defs.name: end
defs.docs: The ending byte offset of the match in the search text.

defs.name: Matches
defs.docs: An iterator of non-overlapping matches for in-memory text.

defs.name: StreamMatches
defs.docs: An iterator of non-overlapping matches for streaming text.

defs.name: MatchesOverlapping
defs.docs: An iterator of overlapping matches for in-memory text.

defs.name: StreamMatchesOverlapping
defs.docs: An iterator of overlapping matches for streaming text.

defs.name: FullAcAutomaton
defs.docs: A complete Aho-Corasick automaton.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Build a new expanded Aho-Corasick automaton from an existing
 Aho-Corasick automaton.

defs.name: StateIdx
defs.docs: The integer type used for the state index.

defs.name: AcAutomaton
defs.docs: An Aho-Corasick finite automaton.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new automaton from an iterator of patterns.

defs.name: with_transitions
defs.docs: Create a new automaton from an iterator of patterns.

defs.name: into_full
defs.docs: Build out the entire automaton into a single matrix.

defs.name: Transitions
defs.docs: An abstraction over state transition strategies.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Return a new state at the given depth.

defs.name: goto
defs.docs: Return the next state index given the next character.

defs.name: set_goto
defs.value: fn (&mut self, alpha: u8, si: StateIdx) -> ()
defs.docs: Set the next state index for the character given.

defs.name: heap_bytes
defs.docs: The memory use in bytes (on the heap) of this set of transitions.

defs.name: for_each_transition
defs.docs: Iterates over each state

defs.name: for_each_ok_transition
defs.docs: Iterates over each non-fail state

defs.name: Dense
defs.docs: State transitions that can be stored either sparsely or densely.

defs.docs: State transitions that are always sparse.
